 key developments in the global regulatory landscape. You have: \u2022 Proven experience as a Head of Compliance or Compliance Officer, preferably within the Cryptocurrency, Payments, e-money or Financial Trading sectors, with a focus on a risk-based approach to compliance. \u2022 Demonstrable experience in establishing and maintaining risk management and internal controls environments within a company. \u2022 Strong experience working alongside financial regulators, professional bodies and professional service providers in multiple jurisdictions including Gibraltar and the UK. \u2022 Knowledge and experience of financial services regulation and legal requirements and controls \u2022 Strong hands-on experience delivering compliance outcomes in various operational areas including, but not limited to, AML, KYC, Data Protection. \u2022 Strong familiarity with industry practices and professional standards \u2022 Appropriate compliance professional certification would be beneficial. \u2022 Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to successfully build and maintain relationships with both internal and external stakeholders. \u2022 Integrity and professional ethics, business acumen, teamwork and attention to detail \u2022 A self-starter who relishes the challenge of working in a fast-paced FinTech business And a bit about us\u2026 We successfully support candidates with career changes within the FinTech industry. We emphasise career development within technology led businesses and ensure that our candidates are fully supported through transition. We are a small and friendly bunch with lots of industry knowledge and experience to share. We believe diversity is what makes our world interesting! Fresh new ideas, thinking and approaches, makes us more effective and efficient and we hold ourselves accountable against diversity objectives. Skills Compliance, MLRO, Risk Compensation Negotiable Apply on CryptoJobs Related jobs you might like Chief Financial